# UI Component Styling Guidelines

## Icon Container Styling

When creating components with icons, follow the consistent styling pattern used across the website:

### Standard Icon Container

```tsx
<div className="absolute flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-slate-100 text-gray-800 dark:bg-slate-900 dark:text-gray-200">
  <IconName className="h-6 w-6" aria-hidden="true" />
</div>
```

**Key requirements:**

- Container: `h-10 w-10` (not h-12 w-12)
- Background: `bg-slate-100 text-gray-800 dark:bg-slate-900 dark:text-gray-200` (neutral colors, not colored backgrounds like bg-yellow-500)
- Icon size: `h-6 w-6`
- Always include `aria-hidden="true"` on decorative icons

## Component Structure Patterns

### Feature Section Layout

Components should follow this consistent structure pattern seen in [monorepo-features.tsx](mdc:libs/website/ui-home/src/lib/monorepo-features.tsx):

```tsx
<div className="relative mt-16 lg:grid lg:grid-cols-2 lg:items-center lg:gap-8">
  <div>
    <h3 className="text-2xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
      Section Title
    </h3>
    <p className="mt-3 text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
      Description text
    </p>

    <dl className="mt-10 space-y-10">{/* Feature items with icons */}</dl>
  </div>

  <div className="mt-10 lg:mt-0">{/* Image or complementary content */}</div>
</div>
```

